{"TopicId":141441,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"Yakovlev Yak-38 [STOCK] (1.0.5)","CreatedByName":"TedwinKnockman66","CreatedById":155882,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-08T13:52:34Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"TedwinKnockman66","CreatedById":155882,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-08T13:52:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe\u00A0Yakovlev Yak-38\u00A0was\u00A0Soviet Naval Aviation\u0027s only operational\u00A0VTOLstrike fighter aircraft, in addition to being its first operational carrier-based fixed-wing aircraft. It was developed specifically for and served almost exclusively on the\u00A0Kiev-class aircraft carriers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFile:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/g0y44k38ft8bo9z/Yak-38.craft?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/g0y44k38ft8bo9z/Yak-38.craft?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAction groups: (1 group) activate vertical engines, (2 group) activate main engines, (3 group) deactivate vertical engines, (4 group) deactivate main engines.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nScreenshots:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Vs9epdY.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/Vs9epdY.png\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022sdg6pVg.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/sdg6pVg.png\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u00229dMyrQU.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/9dMyrQU.png\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Lxs74KE.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/Lxs74KE.jpg\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022RF0pLK7.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/RF0pLK7.jpg\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022THE2O7p.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/THE2O7p.jpg\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u002237F0iCh.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/37F0iCh.jpg\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ZGoMeru.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/ZGoMeru.jpg\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022iNqVadk.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/iNqVadk.jpg\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u00220K79OFX.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/0K79OFX.jpg\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Q32HecA.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/Q32HecA.jpg\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022dKRBRGz.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/dKRBRGz.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn real life:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022AEUaNIk.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/AEUaNIk.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-08T18:47:03Z\u0022 title=\u002206/08/2016 06:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 8, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by TedwinKnockman66\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"He_162","CreatedById":152811,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-08T14:12:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell done! I love it!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pTrevTrevs","CreatedById":131541,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-08T14:18:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice job, although I will never understand why people use the Mk 1 cockpit for something that is supposed to be a bubble canopy. In my opinion it looks like some crazy mashup of a private jet and a high powered fighter jet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter playing Wargame, I\u0027ve learned to love the Yak-38, with it being the only plane the USSR has that can carry napalm.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"He_162","CreatedById":152811,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-08T14:29:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222622218\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141441\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465395493\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022131541\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pTrevTrevs\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, pTrevTrevs said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice job, although I will never understand why people use the Mk 1 cockpit for something that is supposed to be a bubble canopy. In my opinion it looks like some crazy mashup of a private jet and a high powered fighter jet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter playing Wargame, I\u0027ve learned to love the Yak-38, with it being the only plane the USSR has that can carry napalm.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is near impossible to get that nosecone shape without it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pTrevTrevs","CreatedById":131541,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-08T18:21:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222622237\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141441\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465396194\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022He_162\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, He_162 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is near impossible to get that nosecone shape without it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*cough*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/khI6DzI.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022khI6DzI.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSimple, but it works and doesn\u0027t sacrifice the somewhat more authentic cockpit shape.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"He_162","CreatedById":152811,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-08T18:24:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222622580\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141441\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465410065\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022131541\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pTrevTrevs\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, pTrevTrevs said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*cough*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSimple, but it works and doesn\u0027t sacrifice the somewhat more authentic cockpit shape.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy personal opinion says that is pure ugly. However, it also isn\u0027t as skinny as the above fighter, and nothing is sacrificed by not using a bubble canopy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pTrevTrevs","CreatedById":131541,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-08T18:39:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222622585\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141441\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465410244\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022He_162\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, He_162 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy personal opinion says that is pure ugly. However, it also isn\u0027t as skinny as the above fighter, and nothing is sacrificed by not using a bubble canopy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s nothing stopping him or anyone else\u00A0from using the Mk 1 cockpit, but to me it just ruins the \u0022fighter jet look\u0022. For some craft I think it works fine, like th SR-71 or MiG-31, an aerial recon plane and long range interceptor, neither of which necessarily require the good visibility of a strike aircraft such as the Yak (the SR-71 and MiG-31 have solid tops on their canopies instead of bubbles anyway).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHe should use whatever cockpit he wants and if he wants to use that one, there isn\u0027t anything I can do to stop him. We all have different tastes and if he prefers that one, at the end of the day, it\u0027s fine by me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: It appears my point has been misunderstood. I still think that cockpit is\u00A0ugly in that context, but if he wants to use it I\u0027m fine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-09T16:08:13Z\u0022 title=\u002206/09/2016 04:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 9, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by pTrevTrevs\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Castille7","CreatedById":101668,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-08T19:03:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt seems\u00A0there is a fine line with\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Eauthentic\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0and what looks good in KSP, I guess depending on which we prefer we will see it as looking nice or not.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}